\begin_layout Title
Challenges of the Potential
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This note discusses the challenges of the potential problem of the 
\begin_inset Formula $\group$
\end_inset

-invariant theory.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let us breifly review the 
\begin_inset Formula $\group$
\end_inset

-invariant model.
 The superpotentials of the model are
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{W}_{Y}=\covp{Q\bar{u}}{6}\higu+\covp{LN}{6}\higu+\covp{Q\bar{d}}{6}\higd+\Phi\Phi S_{7},
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{W}_{Fam}=\left(\covp{NN}{6}+f\covp{\higu\higd}{6_{1}}\right)\Phi+\covp{\bar{\varphi}\bar{\varphi}^{\prime}}{6}\bar{\Phi}+\Phi\bar{\Phi}S_{7},
\]

\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 is an arbitrary parameter.
 
\begin_inset Formula $Q$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{u}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{d}$
\end_inset

 are the Standard Model fields transforming as 
\begin_inset Formula $\rep{3}$
\end_inset

 in 
\begin_inset Formula $\group$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 is the right-handed neutrino and also transforms as 
\begin_inset Formula $\rep{3}$
\end_inset

.
 The Higgs fields 
\begin_inset Formula $\higu$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\higd$
\end_inset

 transform as 
\begin_inset Formula $\rep{6}$
\end_inset

.
 The familons 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\varphi}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\varphi}^{\prime}$
\end_inset

 are of 
\begin_inset Formula $\rep{\bar{3}}$
\end_inset

 representation.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\Phi$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\Phi}$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{7}$
\end_inset

 are 
\begin_inset Formula $\rep{6}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\rep{6}$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\rep{7}$
\end_inset

 respectively.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We assume that 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{7}$
\end_inset

 field acquire a vev at its 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{T}_{7}$
\end_inset

 singlet component, 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\left\langle S_{7}\right\rangle =\begin{pmatrix}\rep{1}=M_{\Phi}\\
\rep{3}=0\\
\rep{\bar{3}}=0
\end{pmatrix},\label{eq:S7-vev}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

 then 
\begin_inset Formula $\Phi\bar{\Phi}S_{7}$
\end_inset

 coupling become a mass 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{\Phi}\Phi\bar{\Phi}$
\end_inset

.
 Assuming 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{\Phi}$
\end_inset

 is very large, we can integer over 
\begin_inset Formula $\Phi$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\Phi}$
\end_inset

.
 It the leads to two dimension-five terms
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\frac{1}{M_{\Phi}}\left\{ \covp{\covp{NN}{6}\covp{\bar{\varphi}\bar{\varphi}^{\prime}}{6}}{7}\right\} _{1}\label{eq:M-term}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\frac{1}{M_{\Phi}}\left\{ \covp{\covp{\higu\higd}{6}\covp{\bar{\varphi}\bar{\varphi}^{\prime}}{6}}{7}\right\} _{1}.\label{eq:mu-term}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

 When the familon 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\varphi}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{\varphi}^{\prime}$
\end_inset

 obtain vevs 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\left\langle \bar{\varphi}\right\rangle =\left\langle \bar{\varphi}_{3}\right\rangle \begin{pmatrix}\bar{\alpha}\lambda^{8}\\
\lambda^{4}\\
1
\end{pmatrix},\quad\left\langle \bar{\varphi}^{\prime}\right\rangle =\left\langle \bar{\varphi}_{3}^{\prime}\right\rangle \begin{pmatrix}\bar{\alpha}^{\prime}\lambda^{8}\\
\lambda^{4}\\
1
\end{pmatrix},\label{eq:familon-vev}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

we obtain the Majorana matrix and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

 matrix from 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:M-term"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:mu-term"

\end_inset

: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{1}{M_{\Phi}}\left\{ \covp{\covp{NN}{6}\covp{\bar{\varphi}\bar{\varphi}^{\prime}}{6}}{7}\right\} _{1}\to N^{T}\mathcal{M}N,
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{1}{M_{\Phi}}\left\{ \covp{\covp{\higu\higd}{6}\covp{\bar{\varphi}\bar{\varphi}^{\prime}}{6}}{7}\right\} _{1}\to\higu\mathcal{\mu}\higd.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now there is a quetion: how to generate vevs 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:familon-vev"

\end_inset

? The vevs should come from a 
\begin_inset Formula $\group$
\end_inset

-invariant potential 
\begin_inset Formula $V\left(\bar{\varphi},\bar{\varphi}^{\prime},X\right)$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 denotes any other fields in the potential.
 After 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{7}$
\end_inset

 obtain the vev 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:S7-vev"

\end_inset

, there are two cases for the residual symmetry of 
\begin_inset Formula $V\left(\bar{\varphi},\bar{\varphi}^{\prime},X\right)$
\end_inset

: 1) it still has the 
\begin_inset Formula $\group$
\end_inset

 symmetry; 2) its symmetry becomes 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{T}_{7}$
\end_inset

.
 Let us discuss these two cases separately.
 We denote 
\begin_inset Formula $V\left(\bar{\varphi},\bar{\varphi}^{\prime},X\right)$
\end_inset

 of first case as 
\begin_inset Formula $V^{\left(P\right)}\left(\bar{\varphi},\bar{\varphi}^{\prime},X\right)$
\end_inset

 and the one of second case as 
