\uwave off
\noun off
\color none

\begin_inset Formula $V^{\left(T\right)}\left(\bar{\varphi},\bar{\varphi}^{\prime},X\right)$
\end_inset

 for convenience.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
\begin_inset Formula $V^{\left(P\right)}\left(\bar{\varphi},\bar{\varphi}^{\prime},X\right)$
\end_inset

 case
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Because of the 
\begin_inset Formula $\group$
\end_inset

 symmetry, 
\begin_inset Formula $V^{\left(P\right)}$
\end_inset

 is invariant under the transformation
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\bar{\varphi}\to g\bar{\varphi},\quad\bar{\varphi}^{\prime}\to g\bar{\varphi}^{\prime},\quad X\to gX,
\]

\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $g$
\end_inset

 is any member of the 
\begin_inset Formula $\group$
\end_inset

 group.
 It implies that, if 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\langle \bar{\varphi}\right\rangle $
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\langle \bar{\varphi}^{\prime}\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 , and 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\langle X\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 are vevs of 
\begin_inset Formula $V^{\left(P\right)}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $g\left\langle \bar{\varphi}\right\rangle $
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $g\left\langle \bar{\varphi}^{\prime}\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 , and 
\begin_inset Formula $g\left\langle X\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 are also vevs of 
\begin_inset Formula $V^{\left(P\right)}$
\end_inset

.
 However, since 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:M-term"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:mu-term"

\end_inset

 have 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{T}_{7}$
\end_inset

 symmetry but not 
\begin_inset Formula $\group$
\end_inset

 symmetry, the 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

-matrix and Majorana matrix would be changed if 
\begin_inset Formula $g$
\end_inset

 is not the member of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{T}_{7}$
\end_inset

 subgroup.
 Particularly, for the leading order vev of 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:familon-vev"

\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left\langle \bar{\varphi}\right\rangle \sim\begin{pmatrix}0\\
0\\
1
\end{pmatrix},\quad\left\langle \bar{\varphi}^{\prime}\right\rangle \sim\begin{pmatrix}0\\
0\\
1
\end{pmatrix},
\]

\end_inset

 there exists a non 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{T}_{7}$
\end_inset

 transformation producing the vacuum 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left\langle \bar{\varphi}\right\rangle \sim\begin{pmatrix}\sin\frac{\pi}{7}\\
-\cos\frac{\pi}{14}\\
-\cos\frac{3\pi}{14}
\end{pmatrix},\quad\left\langle \bar{\varphi}^{\prime}\right\rangle \sim\begin{pmatrix}\sin\frac{\pi}{7}\\
-\cos\frac{\pi}{14}\\
-\cos\frac{3\pi}{14}
\end{pmatrix}.
\]

\end_inset

 Based on numerical calculation, when 
\begin_inset Formula $r=10$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda=.23$
\end_inset

, such vevs lead to the eigenvalues of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

-matrix as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left\{ -1.07302,0.905958,-0.899693,-0.354736,0.254421,0.167059\right\} .
\]

\end_inset

 All the eigenvalues are of order one, which is not the hierarchy we requre.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In conclusion, the potential after 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{7}$
\end_inset

 obtain vev should not be 
\begin_inset Formula $\group$
\end_inset

-invariant.
\end_layout

